# LoadZone Spec-Driven Workflow

- For non-trivial features, architectural changes, or multi-file refactors, start with a short spec or plan before implementation.
- Specs should record scope, affected files, contracts, test strategy, and open questions.
- Keep specs lightweight and update them when implementation decisions change.
- Before closing a task, verify that code, docs, and tests still match the intended scope.
- If follow-up debt remains, record it explicitly instead of hiding it in comments or memory.
